        "body":  "Codex review: NEEDS_CORRECTION\n\nFinding: live handoff docs still describe only the old Inspector/SaveStatus handoff set after this PR adds `MenuStateHandoff`.\n\nExamples:\n- `crates/editor-egui-host/src/handoff.rs:1-8` still says the host has `InspectorHandoff` + `SaveStatusHandoff` as ?the two latest-only snapshot handoffs? and ?Both are type aliases?, but this PR adds a third host-read latest-only alias, `MenuStateHandoff`.\n- `crates/editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs:288-293` says `EguiHost` owns ?two latest-only snapshot handoffs? connecting shell to host; it now owns inspector, save-status, and menu-state.\n- `crates/editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs:364-367` and `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/mod.rs:676-680` describe `MenuCommandHandoff` as unlike ?the two handoffs above?; there are now three latest-only handoffs above.\n- `crates/editor-shell/src/render_path.rs:211`, `:238`, and `:316-324` still describe init as cloning only `InspectorHandoff` + `SaveStatusHandoff` / ?two handoffs?, omitting the new `MenuStateHandoff` clone and publish wire.\n\nThese are live source docs/comments in the exact surfaces this PR extends. The implementation is otherwise authority-clean in my pass: `PlayState::can_*` is pinned to transition success, `MenuStateSnapshot` is observation-only, shell publishes it on both render paths, and the host only maps command to precomputed bool. Please do a complete stale-prose sweep for the handoff count/listing and widen the current-state docs to include `MenuStateHandoff` where appropriate.\n\nCI note: fmt and architecture lints are green; workspace tests / bench compile / CodeQL Rust were still pending when I first checked.\r\n",
