        "body":  "Codex re-review: NEEDS_CORRECTION\n\nThe handoff-count/listing correction is clean now, including the `/`-separated `MenuCommandHandoff` doc. However, the same set-widening drift remains for the shared observation snapshot set:\n\n- `crates/editor-state/src/lib.rs:21-24` says the dep-neutral read-only observation aggregators are `InspectorSnapshot` / `SaveStatusSnapshot`, but this PR adds `MenuStateSnapshot` as another observation aggregator in the same crate.\n- `crates/editor-state/src/handoff.rs:15-16` says `Handoff\u003cT\u003e` lives in `editor-state` for the same dep-neutrality reason as `InspectorSnapshot` / `SaveStatusSnapshot`; after this PR, `MenuStateSnapshot` should be included in that live listing too.\n- `crates/editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs:90-93` lists the current `rge-editor-state` dependency reasons as `InspectorSnapshot` / `SaveStatusSnapshot` inside their handoffs, but now the host also uses `MenuStateSnapshot` via `MenuStateHandoff`.\n\nThe older `EDITOR-SAVE-STATUS-INDICATOR` dispatch-arc prose in `editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs:62-75` can remain historical; I?m only flagging live module/dependency docs that describe the current shared-type set. Functional design remains approved and CI was green on the previous corrected head; this is another source-doc set-listing cleanup.\r\n",
